# 1. Leo/needのデビュー曲

Employee: Shindo is currently in a meeting. I'll have him come over once it's finished. I ask that you have a seat and wait patiently in the meantime.
Honami: Okay, thank you very much.
Saki: *Sigh* This is so exciting!
Shiho: Aren't you a little too giddy?
Saki: But he said he wanted to talk to all of us. Doesn't that mean it's something important?
Honami: True. We have only been talking to each other through email and video meetings lately.
Ichika: Something important...
Ichika: What if there's been a new development with regards to our debut?
Saki: Oh, yeah! So far, all we know is the date he told us.
Saki: What else could it be...? Maybe we get to perform in that festival?
Honami: Hehe. Both are very exciting prospects.
Shiho: Yeah, I guess you have a point.
Saki: Hehe. I can't wait for Mr. Shindo to get here.
???: Thank you for coming all this way today.
Saki: Oh...!
Ichika: Sounds like Mr. Shindo's finished with his other meeting.
Saki: Yeah! That means he should be here soon.
Shiho: Hm? Huh...?
???: Please give them my regards. We have high hopes for them.
Shiho: Why does that person seem so familiar...?
Saki: Huh?
Shindo: Oh, you're all here. Perfect. Allow me to introduce you.
Shindo: This is Mr. Shimizu, one of the producers for Starry Music...
Shiho: What...?
Saki: Starry Music...? As in THE Starry Music...?!
Shiho: I knew I'd seen you somewhere before...
Shimizu: Oh, you must be Leo/need! Hello, my name is Shimizu.
Honami: I-It's nice to meet you as well. We're Leo/need.
Shiho, Ichika & Saki: Nice to meet you.
Shimizu: Yes, it's nice to finally meet all of you.
Shimizu: I heard that you're going to be playing in Jam Fest. I couldn't believe it when I heard you're already slated to perform in it before making your debut.
Shimizu: I wish you all the best of luck.
Honami: Th-Thank you very much...
Saki: Yes, we plan to do our very best!
Saki: Wait, huh...? We get to play in that festival?!
Shindo: Yes, we'll discuss that in a little bit.
Shimizu: Haha. Sorry, Shindo. I didn't mean to spill the beans like that.
Shimizu: But we have very high hopes for you. After all, you were handpicked by Shindo here.
Shimizu: And he's been a huge help so far.
Ichika: Really...?
Shindo: I appreciate the compliment. And I'm definitely happy about receiving such a big opportunity.
Shimizu: Haha. Call it a win-win.
Shimizu: Oh, look at the time. I need to get going... Again, everyone, good luck!
Honami: Oh...! Thank you very much!
Ichika: Th-That was kind of a surprise...
Shiho: Yeah... I mean, this is a huge company we're talking about...
Saki: More importantly, Mr. Shindo! We really get to play at that festival?!
Shindo: Ah, yes. We came to a decision just the other day during an internal meeting.
Shindo: On one hand, there is still quite a lot you need to work on as a band.
Shindo: But on the other, Ms. Mochizuki's rapid growth over such a short period coupled with your incredible sound made us believe that you'll be ready by the day of.
Honami: ...!
Shindo: You have plenty of time until Jam Fest, so my hope is that you'll be able to use that time to gain more experience and make improvements.
Honami: Right...! Thank you very much!
Saki: We did it, Hona!
Honami: We did...!
Shindo: There's also another important matter I need to discuss with you all today.
Ichika: Huh...?
Shiho: Something else...?
Shindo: I'd like to start working on Leo/need's debut single.
Saki: Our...
Saki: Our debut single?!
Shindo: Yes. Some marketing decisions were also made during the meeting I just mentioned, meaning it's now time to take this step.
Ichika: I see... Well, we are going to need a single if we're going to make our debut.
Saki: Right! And we gotta make it a good one!
Shindo: However, I'd like to make an additional request regarding that...
Honami: An additional request...?
Shindo: Yes.
Shindo: I'd like for you two to write it together, Ms. Tenma, Ms. Hoshino.
Ichika: Oh, okay... I'll write the lyrics and Saki will come up with the music like always...
Shindo: Not quite... I'm talking about you two doing both of those things together.
Ichika & Saki: What...?
